sequenceDiagram
    participant User as CLI User / Automation
    participant CLI as odh-cli<br/>(rhai-cli)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant FS as Local Filesystem

    Note over User, FS: Flow 1: Upgrade Readiness Lint Check

    User->>CLI: rhai-cli lint --target-version 3.5
    CLI->>K8sAPI: GET ClusterVersion, DSC, DSCI, CSVs<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI-->>CLI: Current cluster state
    CLI->>CLI: Select applicable checks<br/>(version-aware targeting)
    loop 38 registered checks (5 groups)
        CLI->>K8sAPI: GET CRDs, Resources per check<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>CLI: Resource data
        CLI->>CLI: Evaluate check (Reader only)
    end
    CLI->>CLI: Render results via Output System<br/>(cli.opendatahub.io/v1 envelope)
    CLI-->>User: Table / JSON / YAML output

    Note over User, FS: Flow 2: Migration Action Execution

    User->>CLI: rhai-cli migrate run --target-version 3.5 --yes
    CLI->>K8sAPI: GET current version, DSC, component state<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI-->>CLI: Platform state
    CLI->>CLI: Select applicable actions<br/>(19 registered, version-filtered)
    loop Applicable migration actions
        CLI->>K8sAPI: PATCH / CREATE / DELETE resources<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>CLI: Mutation result
    end

    opt TrustyAI Metrics Migration
        CLI->>TrustyAI: GET /metrics (backup)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: InsecureSkipVerify
        TrustyAI-->>CLI: Metrics data
        CLI->>TrustyAI: POST /metrics (restore)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        TrustyAI-->>CLI: Restore confirmation
    end

    CLI->>CLI: Record results
    CLI-->>User: Migration report (Table / JSON / YAML)

    Note over User, FS: Flow 3: Workload Backup

    User->>CLI: rhai-cli backup --namespace my-ns
    CLI->>K8sAPI: GET primary resources<br/>(Notebooks, InferenceServices,<br/>RayClusters, etc.)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI-->>CLI: Workload resources
    CLI->>CLI: Resolve dependencies<br/>(ConfigMaps, Secrets, PVCs)
    CLI->>K8sAPI: GET dependent resources<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>CLI: Dependent resources
    CLI->>CLI: Strip server-managed fields
    CLI->>FS: Write YAML files<br/>(parallel resource writer)
    CLI-->>User: Backup summary
